  "text": "In order to generalize Lemma 2.3 to games that do not necessarily have a connected hierarchy, we define the intermediate game (see [CITATION_1] for a similar construction) of (N, , v) as follows. Denote by R (N, ) = R the partition of N whose elements are the connected components of N . In the present context R is considered as natural set of \"a priori unions\" and not a \"coalition structure\"à la Aumann and Drèze Proposition 2.4 For any game (N, , v) with precedence constraints, any preimputation y of the intermediate game (R, v R ), and any α ∈ R,",
